# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Spiral Dynamics MVP - Environment Configuration
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# REQUIRED - Application will not start without these
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Database Connection
# Get a PostgreSQL connection string from:
# - Vercel Postgres: https://vercel.com/storage/postgres
# - Neon: https://neon.tech/
# - Supabase: https://supabase.com/
# - Or use local: postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/spiral_dynamics
POSTGRES_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/spiral_dynamics

# OpenAI API Key
# Used for: Main chat LLM, Interpreter LLM, Insight Model, and embeddings
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...

# Authentication Secret
# Used by NextAuth for session encryption
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET=your-secret-here-generate-with-openssl

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL - Enhances functionality but not required
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Vector Database (ChromaDB)
# Enables RAG context retrieval from belief history
# If not provided, system works but without pixel retrieval in conversations
# Default: none (system continues without RAG)

# Option 1: ChromaDB Cloud (Recommended - https://www.trychroma.com/)
# Get your credentials from ChromaDB Cloud dashboard
CHROMA_TENANT=your-tenant-id
CHROMA_DATABASE=your-database-name
CHROMA_API_KEY=ck-your-api-key

# Option 2: Self-hosted ChromaDB
# Run locally: docker run -p 8000:8000 chromadb/chroma
# CHROMA_URL=http://localhost:8000
# CHROMA_API_KEY=your-token-if-needed

# Distributed Cache (Redis/Upstash)
# Required for production multi-instance deployments
# In development, uses in-memory cache (fine for single instance)
# Get Redis from:
# - Upstash: https://upstash.com/
# - Redis Cloud: https://redis.io/cloud/
# - Vercel KV: https://vercel.com/storage/kv
REDIS_URL=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AUTOMATIC - Usually auto-populated, rarely need manual setting
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Environment
# Automatically set by Node.js/Next.js
# Options: development | production | test
NODE_ENV=development

# Vercel Deployment Variables
# Auto-populated when deployed to Vercel
# No need to set manually
VERCEL=
VERCEL_URL=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DEVELOPMENT ONLY - For local testing
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Custom Port (optional)
# Default: 3000
# PORT=3000

# CI Environment (optional)
# Set by CI systems like GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, etc.
# CI=true

